{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=January 2013}} {{notability|Biographies|date=March 2015}} }} {{Infobox person | name = Franko Luin | image = Franko Luin 2003.png | alt = Franko Luin | caption = Franko Luin | other_names = | occupation = Swedish type designer | birth_place = [[Trieste]], [[Italy]] | death_place = [[Tyresö]], [[Sweden]] | birth_date = {{start-date|April 6, 1941|mf=yes}} | death_date = {{Death-date and age|September 15, 2005|April 6, 1941|mf=yes}} }}
'''Franko Luin''' (April 6, 1941 in [[Trieste]], [[Italy]] &ndash; September 15, 2005 in [[Tyresö]], [[Sweden]]) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] type designer of [[Slovenians|Slovene]] origin. He studied graphic arts at [[Grafiska Institutet]] in Stockholm, where he graduated in 1967. A [[graphic design]]er at the telecom company [[Ericsson]] (1967–1989), He started his own design shop [[Omnibus Typografi]] in 1989.
Franko Luin had a keen interest in languages, particularly the international auxiliary language [[Esperanto]], and was for many years president of the Swedish Esperanto association [[Swedish Esperanto Federation|SEF]]. He wrote poems, translated songs into Esperanto and organized a well renowned homepage, the ''Kiosk'',<ref>''[http://www.esperanto.se/kiosk/ Kiosk]'' list of online newspapers. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071103210608/http://www.esperanto.se/kiosk/ |date=November 3, 2007 }}</ref> which had an enormous link list of online newspapers. In his later years, he collected and digitized many 19th and 20th century works by Slovene classical authors and distributed them on his homepage ''Beseda'' ("Word").<ref>[http://www.omnibus.se/beseda/ Beseda] website {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081219165044/http://www.omnibus.se/beseda/ |date=December 19, 2008 }}</ref>
