'''Opéra bouffon''' is the French term for the Italian genre of [[opera buffa]] (comic opera) performed in 18th-century France, either in the original language or in French translation. The term was also used by [[Jacques Offenbach]] for three of his works: ''[[Orphée aux enfers]]'', ''{{ill|Le roman comique|fr|Le Roman comique (opéra)}}'' and ''[[scores:Le voyage de MM. Dunanan père et fils (Offenbach, Jacques)|Le voyage de MM. Dunanan père et fils'']].

The term is sometimes confused with the French [[opéra comique]] and [[opéra bouffe]].

