{{short description|2014 book by Chad Engelland}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Ostension: Word Learning and the Embodied Mind | image = | caption = | authors = [[Chad Engelland]] | country = | language = English | subject = [[Ostension]] | publisher = [[MIT Press]] | pub_date = 2014 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 336 pp. | isbn = 9780262028097 }}
'''''Ostension: Word Learning and the Embodied Mind''''' is a 2014 book by [[Chad Engelland]] in which the author provides a philosophical introduction to [[Ostension]] and its significance in [[word learning]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Macarthur|first1=David|title=Review of Ostension: Word Learning and the Embodied Mind|journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]]|date=1 June 2016|url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/ostension-word-learning-and-the-embodied-mind/|issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chad Engelland: Ostension: Word Learning and the Embodied Mind|url=http://reviews.ophen.org/2017/05/22/chad-engelland-ostension-word-learning-and-the-embodied-mind/|website=[[Phenomenological Reviews]]|accessdate=17 February 2018|date=22 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chad Engelland, “Ostension: Word Learning and the Embodied Mind” (MIT Press, 2015)|url=http://newbooksnetwork.com/chad-engelland-ostension-word-learning-and-the-embodied-mind-mit-press-2015/|website=[[New Books Network]]|accessdate=18 February 2018|date=14 August 2015}}</ref>
