'''Seán Ó Conghaile''' (1903—18 June 1995<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ainm.ie/Bio.aspx?ID=1648|title=Ó CONGHAILE, Seán (1903–1995)|website=ainm.ie|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>) was an Irish writer.

A native of An Cnoc, [[Cois Fharraige (area)|Cois Fharraige]], [[County Galway]], Ó Conghaile was a celebrated essayist and short-story writer who wrote in the [[Irish language]]. Several of his essays won [[Oireachtas]] prizes, and were collectively published in 1974.

